HOUSE BILL 90
By Haston
SENATE BILL 157
By Hensley
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 49,
relative to accountability.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-228(a), is amended by deleting
subdivision (3) and substituting instead the following:
(3) Other outcome indicators of student achievement that the department finds
to be reliable measures of school performance. If the department uses student
performance on a postsecondary readiness assessment, such as the ACT or SAT, as an
indicator of student achievement for purposes of this subdivision (a)(3), then:
(A) The department shall also use student performance on the career
readiness assessments described in ยง 49-6-6001(b)(4) as an indicator of student
achievement for purposes of this subdivision (a)(3); and
(B) If a student is administered a postsecondary readiness assessment
and a career readiness assessment, then the department shall only consider
student performance on the assessment for which the student achieved the
highest score for purposes of assigning a school letter grade.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2025, the public welfare requiring it, and
applies to school grades issued for the 2025-2026 school year and subsequent school years.
